## Common Tasks

### Starting the Development Server
1. Run `start.bat` (Windows) - automatically handles server selection
2. Server will open browser at `http://localhost:8000`
3. For TypeScript support, ensure Node.js is installed
4. Check `docs/TROUBLESHOOTING.md` if server fails to start

### Adding a New Page
1. Create file in `frontend/src/pages/PageName.tsx`
2. Add route to `AppRoute` enum in `types.ts`
3. Add navigation item in `Layout.tsx` if needed
4. Add case in `App.tsx` renderContent switch

### Adding a New Icon
1. Add icon component to `ICONS` object in `constants.tsx`
2. Use SVG format with proper props
3. Export and use as `<ICONS.IconName />`

### Styling a New Component
1. Start with `glass-card` base class
2. Add spacing with `p-6` or `p-8`
3. Use rounded corners: `rounded-xl` or `rounded-2xl`
4. Add borders: `border border-white/5`
5. Use hover states: `hover:border-purple-500/30`

### Configuring Gemini API
1. Get API key from [Google AI Studio](https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey)
2. Set `window.GEMINI_API_KEY` in `index.html` script section
3. See `docs/API_SETUP.md` for detailed instructions
4. Service automatically falls back to mock responses if no key is set

